The paper presents a deep learning-based framework for automatic seizure type classification using clinical EEG data. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
